  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      When mothers wanted to shift from breast milk to infant formulae, babies were randomly
      assigned to receive a fermented or a standard formula. Biological and clinical investigations
      were achieved at baseline (V1), and after one (V2) and three months (V3) of consumption of
      study formula. Intestinal microbiota was assessed by using culture-dependent techniques.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
